title: The Brothers-In-Law - Expose' 67
description:
The \&#039;Brothers-In-Law\&#039; were a unique, Canadian, folk-satire group formed in the \&#039;60s by some coppers in Windsor, Ontario, Canada.

They were Alec Somervile, Larry Reaume, and my brother, Bob Lee.

Alec is a wonderfull wordsmith - Larry gave me a ticket for speeding when I was a kid, and wound-up singing with my Dad - Bob, God bless him, never figured this bootleg-album would ever wind-up here!

Ya just gotta be a Canuck, or possibly Swede to even like this stuff ... Enjoy 

gonzo5440 ... aka \&#039;baryshery\&#039;
